  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Our hypothesis is that totally Implantable Venous Access Devices in neoplastic patients
      modify body image and self-representation. Therefore, the purpose of this study is to
      evaluate the efficacy of psychological intervention on patients undergone this surgical
      practice.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
